#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.27"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.27:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.27:0.2"
msgid "3. Anuttariyavagga"
msgstr "3. Unsurpassable"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.27:0.3"
msgid "27. Paṭhamasamayasutta"
msgstr "27. Proper Occasions (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "an6.27:1.2"
msgid ""
"“kati nu kho, bhante, samayā manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamitun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how many occasions are there for going to see an esteemed mendicant?”"

msgctxt "an6.27:1.3"
msgid ""
"“Chayime, bhikkhu, samayā manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, there are six occasions for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.318"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:2.1"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.27:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati "
"kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānāti tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā evamassa "
"vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Firstly, there’s a time when a mendicant’s heart is overcome and mired in "
"sensual desire, and they don’t truly understand the escape from sensual "
"desire that has arisen. On that occasion they should go to an esteemed "
"mendicant and say:"

msgctxt "an6.27:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharāmi kāmarāgaparetena, "
"uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘My heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire, and I don’t truly "
"understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen."

msgctxt "an6.27:2.4"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā kāmarāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr "Venerable, please teach me how to give up sensual desire.’"

msgctxt "an6.27:2.5"
msgid "Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu kāmarāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"Then that esteemed mendicant teaches them how to give up sensual desire."

msgctxt "an6.27:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, paṭhamo samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā "
"viharati byāpādaparetena, uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānāti tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā evamassa "
"vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when a mendicant’s heart is overcome and mired "
"in ill will …"

msgctxt "an6.27:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharāmi byāpādaparetena, "
"uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:3.3"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā byāpādassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:3.4"
msgid "Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu byāpādassa pahānāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:3.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, dutiyo samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (2)"
msgstr "This is the second occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena "
"cetasā viharati thinamiddhaparetena, uppannassa ca thinamiddhassa nissaraṇaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā "
"evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when a mendicant’s heart is overcome and mired "
"in dullness and drowsiness …"

msgctxt "an6.27:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharāmi "
"thinamiddhaparetena, uppannassa ca thinamiddhassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:4.3"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā thinamiddhassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:4.4"
msgid "Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu thinamiddhassa pahānāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, tatiyo samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (3)"
msgstr "This is the third occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.319"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena "
"cetasā viharati uddhaccakukkuccaparetena, uppannassa ca uddhaccakukkuccassa "
"nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu "
"upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when a mendicant’s heart is overcome and mired "
"in restlessness and remorse …"

msgctxt "an6.27:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharāmi "
"uddhaccakukkuccaparetena, uppannassa ca uddhaccakukkuccassa nissaraṇaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:5.3"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā uddhaccakukkuccassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:5.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu uddhaccakukkuccassa pahānāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:5.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, catuttho samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā "
"viharati vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā "
"evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when a mendicant’s heart is overcome and mired "
"in doubt …"

msgctxt "an6.27:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ, āvuso, vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharāmi vicikicchāparetena, "
"uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:6.3"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā vicikicchāya pahānāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:6.4"
msgid "Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu vicikicchāya pahānāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.27:6.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, pañcamo samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

# BB has “object” for nimitta: “what object to rely on and attend to in order to attain …” But there is no such thing as a meditation “object” in early Buddhism. A nimitta is the very antithesis of an object; it is constantly associated with saññā, with perception, with ways of seeing, with aspects of things. To focus on a nimitta is to pay attention to that aspect of experience, especially meditative experience, that fosters and grows the requisite qualities, **together with the attending mind**, not as an object of it. The idiom yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto recurs at MN 20, where BB renders it “when a bhikkhu is giving attention to some sign, and owing to that sign…” Nyanamoli had: “owing to some sign, to which sign he is giving attention”. BB’s more recent translation duplicates the sense of “owing to” (āgamma). I don’t try top capture the repeated yam, but try to capture the sense.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ "
"nimittaṃ manasikaroto anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti taṃ nimittaṃ nappajānāti "
"tasmiṃ samaye manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when a mendicant doesn’t understand what kind of "
"meditation to focus on in order to end the defilements in the present life. "
"On that occasion they should go to an esteemed mendicant and say:"

msgctxt "an6.27:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto anantarā "
"āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, taṃ nimittaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘I don’t understand what kind of meditation to focus on in order to end the "
"defilements in the present life."

msgctxt "an6.27:7.3"
msgid "Sādhu vata me āyasmā āsavānaṃ khayāya dhammaṃ desetū’ti."
msgstr "Venerable, please teach me how to end the defilements.’"

msgctxt "an6.27:7.4"
msgid "Tassa manobhāvanīyo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr "Then that esteemed mendicant teaches them how to end the defilements."

msgctxt "an6.27:7.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhu, chaṭṭho samayo manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ. (6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth occasion for going to see an esteemed mendicant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.27:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhu, cha samayā manobhāvanīyassa bhikkhuno dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamitun”ti."
msgstr "These are the six occasions for going to see an esteemed mendicant.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.27:8.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
